In the previous post in this series, we added a new "virtual" field to our GraphQL schema for Post, related:
 

type Post {
  id: ID!
  title: String!
  url: Url!
  date: Date
  tags: [String!]!
  description: String
  content: String!
  related(tag: String): [Post!]
}

 
But in doing so, we added a problem, let's take this query as an example:
 

query {
  posts {
    related {
      related {
        related {
          related {
            related {
              related {
                related {
                  related {
                    title
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 
